<hr>
<h2>History of Present Illness</h2>
<p>Mr. Michael Thompson, a 54-year-old male, presented to the emergency department with progressive shortness of breath, fever (up to 102&deg;F), and productive cough with yellow-green sputum for the last 5 days. He reports chest pain that worsens with deep inspiration and fatigue that limits daily activities.</p>
<p>The patient was initially self-medicating with acetaminophen, but his symptoms worsened. On the day of admission, he developed dizziness and worsening dyspnea, prompting hospital visit.</p>
<p>No history of hemoptysis or recent travel. No known tuberculosis exposure.</p>
