<ol>
<li>
<p>Admit to inpatient pulmonology service</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Start empiric IV antibiotics: Ceftriaxone + Azithromycin</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Oxygen supplementation via nasal cannula (2&ndash;4 L/min) to maintain SpO₂ &gt;94%</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Monitor vitals, pulse oximetry, and blood cultures</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Incentive spirometry and chest physiotherapy for airway clearance</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Strict glycemic control with insulin sliding scale during infection</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Antipyretics for fever (acetaminophen PRN)</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>IV fluids for hydration</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Educate patient and family regarding pneumonia, antibiotic adherence, and smoking cessation reinforcement</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Plan for follow-up chest X-ray in 6 weeks post-discharge</p>
</li>
</ol>
